 — filter for GPT models only\n- Anthropic: `GET https://api.anthropic.com/v1/models` (x-api-key header)  \n- Google: `GET https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=...`\n\n**Deprecated model handling:**\n- After fetching, compare user's saved model against the live list\n- If not found: inject `{ value: savedModel, label: \"⚠ [model-name] (Deprecated)\", deprecated: true }` as first item in the dropdown\n- Show a HeroUI `<Alert color=\"warning\">` in the settings UI: \"Your configured model [X] is no longer available. Please select a different model.\"\n\n**Cache structure** in `chrome.storage.local`:\n```ts\nmodelCache: {\n  [provider: string]: {\n    models: string[];\n    fetchedAt: number; // timestamp\n    ttl: number;       // 24h in ms\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Trigger:** Fetch is triggered automatically when the user saves a new API key (`SET_CONFIG` handler). Also fetched on demand when settings page opens (if cache is stale).\n\n---\n\nThis plan is fairly large. Here's my recommended sequencing:\n\n1. Task 1 (input type fix) — quick win, 15 min\n2. Task 2 (scroll positioning) — quick fix, 30 min  \n3. Task 4 (HeroUI setup) — do this before building options page\n4. Task 3 (options page) — biggest task, 2-3h\n5. Task 5 (onboarding) — depends on options page\n6. Task 6 (model fetching) — depends on options page + settings view\n\nDoes this plan look right? Any adjustments before I start implementing?",
