          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "All done. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**HeroUI CSS missing (dark theme + tab selected states)**\n\nThe two CSS files were missing two required directives from the HeroUI Tailwind v4 setup guide:\n\n```css\n@source \"../../../../node_modules/@heroui/theme/dist/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}\";\n@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark *));\n```\n\n- `@source` — tells Tailwind v4 to scan HeroUI's theme dist for class names like `data-[selected=true]:bg-primary`, `data-[focused=true]:outline`, etc. Without this, no HeroUI component interactive states were emitted (hence no tab selected indicator, no checkbox/switch styling).\n- `@custom-variant dark` — wires the `dark:` utility prefix to respond to `.dark` on an ancestor element (which `useTheme` sets on `<html>`). Without this, `dark:` utilities were inactive. The CSS went from 53KB → 251KB confirming all the missing styles are now included.\n\n**Scroll at window edge**\n\nRemoved `max-w-4xl mx-auto` from the Tabs container. The tab list row now uses `max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6` on the `tabList` classname slot. Each tab panel wraps its view in a `<div className=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full px-6\">` so content is constrained but the scrollbar sits at the viewport edge.\n\n**Footer button alignment**\n\n- `SettingsView`: removed `w-full` from the Save button, wrapped in `flex justify-end`\n- `SkillEditor`: added `justify-end` to the footer div, reordered to Cancel → Save (primary action last)",
